## 13. LANGUAGE AND TERMINOLOGY

*(Full detail in `academic_writing_guide.md`. These are the minimum standards.)*

- Publication-level quality: no systematic grammar or spelling errors.
- Technical terminology is correct and applied consistently.
- Clear, precise sentences without nominalization or inflated phrasing.
- No stylistic inconsistency between chapters.
- The same concept is always referred to by the same term.

