## 14. WHAT SEPARATES A DISTINCTION FROM A MERIT

| Criterion | Merit (2,0) | Distinction (1,0) |
|---|---|---|
| Research question | Present but broad | Precise, bounded, operationalized |
| Independent contribution | Literature synthesis with own commentary | Identifiable contribution of one of the recognized types |
| Methodology | Named and applied | Justified, reflected, with explicit limitation discussion |
| Reproducibility | Results are plausible | Procedure fully documented, independently assessable |
| Argumentation | Coherent | Gapless, consistent, self-critical, separates results from interpretation |
| Literature | Relevant and correctly cited | Current, international, critically contextualized |
| Language | Clear and understandable | Publication-level, precise, terminologically consistent |
| IS specificity | Technical OR managerial | Interdisciplinary, practice implications integrated |
| Critical reflection | Present | Systematic across all four limitation levels |
| Evaluation (design work) | Conducted | Criteria-based, context-appropriate, weaknesses reported |
| Ethics and data management | Basic compliance | Fully documented: consent, anonymization, storage, disclosure |
